<TITLE> Govt to aid boat victims, Kishoreganj toll rises to 48 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kishoreganj, Dec 05 (bdnews24,com)  The government will give Tk 30,000 to each family of victims of Friday's boat capsize as one more body was recovered from Daira river on Saturday raising the death toll to 48. The accident took place at around 9:30am Friday when a Bhairab-bound engine boat collided with passenger ferry MV Al-Helal near Charigram in Mithamoin upazila of Kishoreganj. Mithamoin Upazilla Nirbahi Officer Gopal Chandra Das said the body recovered Saturday is of a child named Sohag Chowdhury, 9. Mithamoin thana police sub inspector Abdul Motaleb filed a case on Friday over the boat capsize incident. After inspecting the spot, Bangladesh Inland Water Transport Authority (BIWTA) chairman Abdul Malek Mia said a high power committee has been formed with water transport ministry's joint secretary Md Abdul Quddus as head to find out the cause of the boat capsize. Meanwhile, Kishoreganj district commissioner Md Shah Kamal said that a three-member committee has been formed with additional district commissioner Tulsi Ranjan Das as its head and Tk 2,000 will be given to each of the families on behalf of the district commission. bdnews24.com/corr/mus
